Allied Irish Appoints Ronan O’Neill as Head of U.K. Division

-- B y   J o e   B r e n n a n
-- 
2011-10-03T09:27:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/allied-irish-appoints-ronan-o-neill-as-head-of-u-k-division.html
Allied Irish Banks Plc (ALBK)  said it
appointed Ronan O’Neill, currently head of corporate and
commercial banking, as managing director of the lender’s U.K.
division.  O’Neill will also join AIB’s executive committee, the
Dublin-based bank said in an e-mailed statement today.  Nick Treble will become head of the bank’s non-core U.K.
operation “and will have responsibility for a number of
strategic initiatives relating to the development of the U.K.
business,” the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
